[Groovy] Class startExec

java.lang.Object
  startExec

class startExec

Description:
This is the main class of the project and one of the below constructors need to be invoked to be able to use this jar file functionality. Functionality that can be invoked from this class is as follows.
  • Capture URLs from responses, generate label images, and save them.
  • Capture Responses from SoapUI TestRequests and save them.
  • Capture DataSinks from SoapUI and save their contents to a CSV or Pipe Delimited file.
Authors:
Diganth Aswath

startExec

startExec(java.lang.Object context, java.lang.Object propertyName)
Constructor 1
Parameters:
context - This is the SoapUI Context parameter that needs to be passed in for the jar file to access SoapUI components.

propertyName - There are 2 possible values for this string variable
  • "Project" - This string directs the jar file to look for "ResultFilePath" property in SoapUI Project properties.
  • TestStepPropertyName - This directs the jar file to look for "ResultFilePath" property in SoapUI property test step mentioned.

      startExec

      startExec(java.lang.Object context, java.lang.Object testRunner, java.lang.Object propertyName, java.lang.Object captureType)
      Constructor 3
      Parameters:
      context - This is the SoapUI Context parameter required for the jar file to access SoapUI components.
      testRunner - This is the SoapUI TestRunner paramater required for the jar file to access SoapUI components.

      propertyName - There are 2 possible values for this string variable
      • "Project" - This string directs the jar file to look for "ResultFilePath" property in SoapUI Project properties.
      • TestStepPropertyName - This directs the jar file to look for "ResultFilePath" property in SoapUI property test step mentioned.

      captureType - There are 2 possible values for this string variable
      • "Response" - This string directs the jar file to only capture Responses from the Test Requests.
      • "URL" - This string directs the jar file to only capture URL's from the responses of Test Requests and generate label images.

         
        Method Detail

        captureDataSink

        java.lang.Object captureDataSink(java.lang.Object dataSinkName)
        Function is used to capture SoapUI DataSink and store them in .csv files. This function requires the presence of a SoapUI TestCase property "CSVHeader" with value 0 to capture the DataSink Column Headers. If the TestCase property is missing, the .csv file created will not contain column headers.
        Parameters:
        dataSinkName - This is the name of the SoapUI data sink testStep to be captured.

        captureDataSinkPipe

        java.lang.Object captureDataSinkPipe(java.lang.Object dataSinkName)
        Function is used to capture SoapUI DataSink and store them in "|" delimited '.dat' files. This function requires the presence of a SoapUI TestCase property "PIPEHeader" with value 0 to capture the DataSink Column Headers. If the TestCase property is missing, the .dat file created will not contain column headers.
        Parameters:
        dataSinkName - This is the name of the SoapUI data sink testStep to be captured.
